[2026-07-19 04:09:41 PDT] Cloudflare deployment incident and fix

Observed failure:
- Cloudflare build c65ba189-3fff-4e6f-9ccd-f5906541ec8c built the application and uploaded 19 assets.
- Worker version creation failed with Cloudflare validation code 10021.
- Exact actionable message: Compatibility flag specified multiple times: nodejs_compat.

Five-whys root-cause analysis:
1. Why did deployment fail? Cloudflare rejected a duplicated compatibility flag.
2. Why was nodejs_compat duplicated? Both vite.config.ts and the generated Wrangler deployment configuration declared it.
3. Why did two configurations own the same setting? The local starter configuration predated Vinext's generated Cloudflare deployment configuration.
4. Why was this not caught by the local build? Vite accepts the merged configuration during compilation; the Cloudflare versions API performs the duplicate validation at deployment time.
5. Why could this recur? There was no checked-in Wrangler configuration or regression assertion establishing a single owner for compatibility flags.

Root-cause correction:
- Removed compatibility_flags from the local Cloudflare Vite plugin configuration.
- Generated and checked in wrangler.jsonc as the single deployment source for nodejs_compat.
- Added a regression test requiring zero declarations in vite.config.ts and exactly one in wrangler.jsonc.

Verification:
- The regression test failed before the fix with the expected duplicate declaration.
- npm run lint: PASS.
- npm test after removing the redundant flag: PASS (3/3 tests).
- npm run deploy -- --dry-run: PASS; produced one nodejs_compat declaration in wrangler.jsonc.
